snippet.textDisplay: A tip for everyone, after you open a new can of paint, punch a few holes in the recessed rim of the can, where the lip of the lid seats.  This will allow the paint in that recessed area to drain back into the can when you tap the lid back on.  This will also help make the lid a bit easier to remove later.
